~| agent-obvious.nox
 |  Demonstration of the "obvious" scripting surface for coding Agents.
 |  Per the two-versions idea: this layer (cli-stdlib + core) should feel natural
 |  for maintaining working memory (maps), exploration, capitalization, etc.
 |  The complex COP/artifacts/judgment version is the other (non-obvious) layer.
 |  Note: some higher helpers (remember/with-update/inc-field! using the keyword
 |  > > forms + map.put) currently hit VM type asserts in primitive_map_put due
 |  to map header/reference expectations and local binding interactions.
 |  The raw primitives (map.new + map.! + map.?@ + /key tags) work for basic cases.
 |  The declarations in cli-stdlib.nox express the intended obvious surface.
 |~

"=== obvious agent scripting demo (raw primitives for now) ===" out "\n" out

~~ Working memory as map (belief state)
map.new >memory
"start" /phase $memory map.!
42 /budget $memory map.!

"initial phase=" out /phase $memory map.?@ out " budget=" out /budget $memory map.?@ out "\n" out

~~ Update (direct map.!)
"working" /phase $memory map.!
1 /budget $memory map.?@ + /budget $memory map.!

"after update phase=" out /phase $memory map.?@ out " budget=" out /budget $memory map.?@ out "\n" out

~~ Branch (separate map for a path in exploration)
map.new >branch
"exploring-A" /phase $branch map.!
100 /budget $branch map.!

"branch phase=" out /phase $branch map.?@ out " budget=" out /budget $branch map.?@ out "\n" out
"parent unchanged phase=" out /phase $memory map.?@ out "\n" out

~~ Record-style (map + convention)
map.new >task
"explore-rational" /name $task map.!
23 /id $task map.!

"name=" out /name $task map.?@ out " id=" out /id $task map.?@ out "\n" out

~~ (Higher obvious helpers like recall/remember/with-update/fork-memory/inc-field!
~~  and the begin-turn/commit/obsolete pattern are declared in cli-stdlib.nox
~~  as the target "obvious for Agents" surface. They layer on the same primitives
~~  once the map/reference/keyword-binding details are solid.)

"(higher helpers declared in cli-stdlib for the obvious agent style; raw map.! works today)" out "\n" out

"demo complete - scripting layer is the obvious one per the two-versions idea" out "\n" out
0 exit
